Methods in Java:
Methods /Function /Behaviours are blocks of code .Thy contain statement(lines of code) which are executed when a method

is called .
A method in Java has a return type (output) name and parameters/argument

Why should we use methods ?
Methods help us the code .When we need to share / reuse a piece  of code within  our project or with oyhers
 we can create our own classes define methods
inside  those classes and we can start reusing/sharing them.
Syntax of the method:
returnType(output) nameOfTheMethod(input/parameters){


}